{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 19, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["kubernetes", "kubernetes", "19e28923070fc6d206ab911e8b4e339dcc08d8d4"], "url": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/commit/19e28923070fc6d206ab911e8b4e339dcc08d8d4", "semantic_text": "[secure-transport] add `~SecureTransport()` destructor (#11562)\n\nThis commit adds a destructor for `SecureTransport` that closes the\nsocket, and disconnects and removes any tracked sessions.\n\nRemoving the sessions ensures that the `SecureSession` instances and\nany data allocated within them are properly freed. This handles the\ncase where the `otInstance` itself is destroyed, ensuring that all\nheap-allocated items are cleaned up correctly to prevent memory\nleaks.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1630486617.0}
